Sentencas: In this study, Gd0.1Ln0.1Ce0.8O2-& alpha; (Ln = Er, Yb) was prepared by a glycine-nitrate combustion method.
Titulo: Effect of ZnO on the intermediate-temperature electrochemical properties of Gd0.1Ln0.1Ce0.8O2-α (Ln = Er, Yb) for solid oxide membrane fuel cells

Sentencas: The influences of the calcining temperature, codoped ion and addition of sintering additive on the structures, grain sizes and intermediate-temperature electrochemical properties of the samples were investigated.
Titulo: Effect of ZnO on the intermediate-temperature electrochemical properties of Gd0.1Ln0.1Ce0.8O2-α (Ln = Er, Yb) for solid oxide membrane fuel cells

Sentencas: The micromorphologies and crystal structures of the synthesized samples were analyzed using scanning electron microscopy (SEM) and X-ray diffraction (XRD).
Titulo: Effect of ZnO on the intermediate-temperature electrochemical properties of Gd0.1Ln0.1Ce0.8O2-α (Ln = Er, Yb) for solid oxide membrane fuel cells

Sentencas: The relationship between the conductivity and oxygen partial pressure and the H2/O2 fuel cell was also studied.
Titulo: Effect of ZnO on the intermediate-temperature electrochemical properties of Gd0.1Ln0.1Ce0.8O2-α (Ln = Er, Yb) for solid oxide membrane fuel cells

Sentencas: The XRD results showed that the samples were single-phase cubic fluorite structures after being calcined at 1350 degrees C and 1450 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of ZnO on the intermediate-temperature electrochemical properties of Gd0.1Ln0.1Ce0.8O2-α (Ln = Er, Yb) for solid oxide membrane fuel cells

Sentencas: The sintering additive of ZnO can significantly affect the morphology and density of the obtained ceria electrolytes.
Titulo: Effect of ZnO on the intermediate-temperature electrochemical properties of Gd0.1Ln0.1Ce0.8O2-α (Ln = Er, Yb) for solid oxide membrane fuel cells

Sentencas: The conductivities of 1350-GEDC-ZnO and 1350-GYDC-ZnO reached 4.4 x 10-2 S cm- 1 and 3.4 x 10-2 S cm- 1 at 750 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Effect of ZnO on the intermediate-temperature electrochemical properties of Gd0.1Ln0.1Ce0.8O2-α (Ln = Er, Yb) for solid oxide membrane fuel cells

Sentencas: The output performance of the intermediate-temperature thin film fuel cell was also studied by applying the electrolyte with the best electrical property.
Titulo: Effect of ZnO on the intermediate-temperature electrochemical properties of Gd0.1Ln0.1Ce0.8O2-α (Ln = Er, Yb) for solid oxide membrane fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum output power densities of the 1350-GEDC-ZnO membrane (15 & mu;m) using Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-& delta; (BSCF) as the cathode were 296.2 mW cm-2, 406.2 mW cm-2 and 529.1 mW cm-2 at 650 degrees C, 700 degrees C and 750 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Effect of ZnO on the intermediate-temperature electrochemical properties of Gd0.1Ln0.1Ce0.8O2-α (Ln = Er, Yb) for solid oxide membrane fuel cells
